Run an R script

USAGE:
    ir run [Rscript-options...] [--with <pkg>]... [--r-version <spec>] <script.R> [args...]
    ir run [Rscript-options...] [--with <pkg>]... [--r-version <spec>] -e <expr> [-e <expr>]... [args...]

`ir run` reads the YAML frontmatter from <script.R>, resolves its
dependencies, builds a dedicated package library, and runs the script
against it. With -e it instead evaluates inline R expressions (mirroring
Rscript) against the same isolated library. --r-version selects the R
version with rig and overrides script frontmatter. Leading Rscript options
are passed to Rscript for the user-code phase; trailing args are passed
through to the program.

OPTIONS:
    -e <expr>     Evaluate an inline R expression instead of a script file.
                  May be repeated; runs in place of <script.R>.
    --with <pkg>  Add a dependency for this run, merged with any declared
                  in the script frontmatter. May be repeated and accepts a
                  comma-separated list (e.g. --with dplyr,tidyr). Uses the
                  same spec format as `dependencies:` (e.g. cli==3.6.6).
    --r-version <spec>
                  Select the R version for this run with rig. Overrides
                  `r-version:` in script frontmatter.

ENVIRONMENT:
    IR_CACHE_DIR   override the cache dir (default: tools::R_user_dir("ir", "cache"))
    IR_RSCRIPT     path to the Rscript executable (default: Rscript on PATH)
